a rather crude object, for all the hushed whispers it has commanded. My thoughtful reverie is broken by a horrific wail of pain... The Ice-Giant is dead, and the time has come to flee. But there will be a time of reckoning. With a quick nick to my hand, one crimson droplet frozen to the cavern floor seals my word upon this foul place. There will come a time of vengeance. That, at least, brings a tight grin to my face. Stealing down a passageway seemingly undiscovered by the giant lords of this castle gripped by Permanent Frost, sneaking away as a theif and not gloriously emerging as befitting a conqueror... The fate of this place has been sealed indeed, and I count the days until my return. Upon my exit, I find the Paladin alive, he tells me the Monk has wisely chosen to return to Karana. Sindarren, the Woodelf, is also here, having been resurrected by a magnanimous Cleric, and is with the Paladin, nursing memories of the cold chill of Death. These brothers-in-battle of mine shall have their time of vengeance with me, and with that we leave. Cold, beaten, but not broken. No, not beaten while the fire of retribution burns within us.~<br>
<br>
<b>Chromehammer Daemonem</b><br>
